{"questionId":"22441859","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>On the same day, the height of water at the second island, Rockall, is modelled by the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the number of hours after midnight, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The first low tide occurs at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>02</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>41</mn></math> when the height of the water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The first high tide occurs at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>09</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>02</mn></math> when the height of the water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>74</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> In part (d), award the marks for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> independent of each other.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find time between low and high tide in hours&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math> hours and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn></math> minutes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn></math> hours</p>\n<p>(period =) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>494739</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>495</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>60</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>381</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find mean of low and high tide times OR substitute values of a known point&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR eg&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>495</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68333</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>85833</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Award <strong>(M1)A0</strong> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>84</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting at least one point into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">h</mi><mrow><mo mathvariant=\"bold\" stretchy=\"true\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">t</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\" stretchy=\"true\">)</mo></mrow></math>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>74</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>AND</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> accept any angles of the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>k</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>k</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>use of graph or table to find their intersection&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to solve their equations simultaneously&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>60</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8533</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>494739</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>495</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22441859","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.8d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the values of a, b, c and d.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}